        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 7:10PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Farmville, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Reduced visibility and minor flooding
possible. Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Farmville and Longwood University around 715 PM EDT.
Rice around 720 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Raines Tavern, Tuggle,
Prince Edward Station, Twin Lakes State Park, Burkes Tavern,
Scholfield, Moran, Kingsville, Reeds, and Jennings Ordinary.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
